---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---
<BaseLayout title="About" description="About The Forwarding Table — a technical networking blog by Michael.">
  <div class="about-page">
    <a href={base} class="back-link">← All posts</a>
    <h1>About</h1>
    <div class="about-content">
      <p>
        I'm Michael — a Network Engineer with over five years of hands-on experience in enterprise
        infrastructure. My focus is on routing and switching, BGP, overlay networks, and the kind
        of operational troubleshooting that only comes from time spent in the trenches.
      </p>

      <h2>What I Do</h2>
      <p>
        On any given day I might be replacing old hardware, tuning EIGRP, standing up a VXLAN/EVPN
        fabric, writing a Python script to automate a provisioning task, or digging into a Palo Alto
        firewall policy. I've delivered data center migrations and core infrastructure replacements
        with zero downtime, and I work directly with customers and vendors to track problems down to
        root cause rather than symptoms.
      </p>
      <p>
        My platform experience spans Cisco IOS/IOS XE/NX-OS, Nexus 5K/7K/9K, Catalyst 9K series,
        ISR/ASR routers, Palo Alto PAN-OS, Fortinet FortiGate, and cloud connectivity on Azure and AWS.
      </p>

      <h2>Certifications</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>CCNP Enterprise</strong> — Cisco Certified Network Professional</li>
        <li><strong>CCNA</strong> — Cisco Certified Network Associate</li>
        <li><strong>CCNA Automation</strong></li>
        <li><strong>Fortinet NSE 3</strong></li>
        <li><strong>Microsoft Azure</strong></li>
      </ul>

      <h2>About This Blog</h2>
      <p>
        This is where I write about what I'm actively working on, studying, and figuring out. Some
        posts are detailed technical write-ups, others are lab notes or half-formed ideas still in
        progress — but all of it comes from real experience, not documentation rewrites.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you're interested in enterprise networking, routing protocols, or the details that live
        a few layers below the surface, you're in the right place.
      </p>

      <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
      <p>
        Feel free to reach out at <a href="mailto:michael.becze@gmail.com">michael.becze@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
